\cf0 The fragmentation ratio is 
\f2\fs26 1.0 - (largest free block / total free memory)
\f1\fs24 . A value of 0.0 means all free memory is in one contiguous block and fully usable. A value of 0.34 means roughly a third of the free memory is split into fragments too small to satisfy most requests.\
The buddy system wins on throughput across every pattern because it avoids linear list scanning. The cost is that internal fragmentation on random-size workloads (0.28) is high due to size rounding. First-fit is fastest of the linked-list strategies but fragments the most. Best-fit is a middle ground: slightly slower than first-fit but noticeably better fragmentation on mixed workloads.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
